&lt;p&gt;Graduated in 2011;&amp;nbsp;completed the requirements for Bachelors of Science (Sc.B.) in Computer Science and Applied Math and Bachelors of Arts (A.B.) in&amp;nbsp;Economics, with excellent marks (i.e., mostly &amp;quot;A&amp;quot;s)&amp;nbsp;although&amp;nbsp;Brown does not officially compute a GPA. Named CAP fellow in Fall 2008 and nominated for membership to Sigma Xi in Spring 2011.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 style=&quot;margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px&quot;&gt;Delbarton School; Morristown, NJ&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Graduated in 2007; highest honors, National Merit Scholarship, University of Pennsylvania Book Award, Delbarton Medal for achievements in Computer Science. Editor-in-chief of&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The Courier&lt;/em&gt;, the school newspaper. Cantor and tenor in 3 music groups spanning plainsong from before the 15th century to modern choral arrangements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

